Title: Production of doubly charmed baryons in B decays Abstract: We study the doubly charmed baryonic B decays $B\to \Xi_{c} \Lambda_{c}$ and
$B\to \Lambda^{+}_{c} \Lambda^{-}_{c} K$, recently observed by BELLE. We find
that the unexpected large branching ratios (BRs) could be ascribed to the final
state interactions (FSIs), which are dictated by $B\to DD^{+}_{s}\to \Xi_{c}
\Lambda^{+}_{c}$ and $B\to \bar D^0 D^{0} K\to \Lambda^{+}_{c} \Lambda^{-}_{c}
K$. By utilizing the same mechanism, we predict that the BRs for $B^{+}\to \bar
\Xi^{0}_{c} \Sigma^{+}_{c}$ and $B^{+} \to \Sigma^{\mp}_{c} \Lambda^{\pm}_{c}
K^{+}$ decays could be as large as $BR(B^{+}\to \bar\Xi^{0}_{c}
\Lambda^{+}_{c})$ and $10^{-4}$, respectively. In addition, extending the FSIs
to the processes associated with the creation of the $s\bar s$ pair,
$BR(B^{+}\to \bar \Omega_{c} \Xi^{+}_{c})$ at percent level is achievable.
